161  void insert(const double timeData, const std::vector<double>& posData)
162  {
163  if (timeVec.empty())
164  timeInit = ros::Time::now().toNSec() * 1e-9;
165 
166  timeVec.push_back(timeData - timeInit);
167  for (uint velType = 0; velType < posVec.size(); ++velType)
168  posVec[velType].push_back(posData[velType]);
169 
170  if (timeVec.size() > maxDataSize)
171  {
172  timeVec.erase(timeVec.begin());
173  for (uint velType = 0; velType < posVec.size(); ++velType)
174  posVec[velType].erase(posVec[velType].begin());
175  }
176  }
177 
178  bool isReadyToEstimate() { return (timeVec.size() == maxDataSize); }
179 
180  double estimate(uint velType)
181  {
182  double velEst = estimateVelocity(timeVec, posVec[velType]);
183  ROS_DEBUG("Estimated velocity type %d = %f", velType, velEst);
184 
185 #ifdef DEBUG_ESTIMATOR
186  std::ostringstream oss_time;
187  oss_time << "timeVec = [ ";
188  for(uint i=0; i < timeVec.size(); ++i)
189  oss_time << timeVec[i] << " ";
190  oss_time << "]";
191 
192  std::ostringstream oss_pos;
193  oss_pos << "posVec[" << velType << "] = [ ";
194  for(uint i=0; i < posVec[velType].size(); ++i)
195  oss_pos << posVec[velType][i] << " ";
196  oss_pos << "]";
197 
198  ROS_DEBUG("%s", oss_time.str().c_str());
199  ROS_DEBUG("%s", oss_pos.str().c_str());
200 #endif
201  return velEst;
202  }
203  } targetVelocityEstimator;

260  void reset()
261  {

356  PFinitData(const uint nParticles, const uint nTargets,
357  const uint statesPerRobot, const uint nRobots,
358  const uint nLandmarks, const std::vector<bool>& robotsUsed,
359  const std::vector<Landmark>& landmarksMap,
360  const std::vector<float>& alpha = std::vector<float>())
361  : nParticles(nParticles), nTargets(nTargets),
362  statesPerRobot(statesPerRobot), nRobots(nRobots),
363  nLandmarks(nLandmarks), alpha(alpha), robotsUsed(robotsUsed),
364  landmarksMap(landmarksMap)
365  {
366  // If vector alpha is not provided, use a default one
367  if (this->alpha.empty())
368  {
369  for (int r = 0; r < nRobots; ++r)
370  {
371  this->alpha.push_back(0.015);
372  this->alpha.push_back(0.1);
373  this->alpha.push_back(0.5);
374  this->alpha.push_back(0.001);
375  }
376  }
377 
378  // Check size of vector alpha
379  if (this->alpha.size() != 4 * nRobots)
380  {
381  ROS_ERROR(
382  "The provided vector alpha is not of the correct size. Returning "
383  "without particle filter! (should have %d=nRobots*4 elements)",
384  nRobots * 4);
385  return;
386  }
387  }
388  };
